value.name: Percentage Calculators from The Calculator Site
value.snippet: Our first step is to change the percentage figure into a decimal. We do this by dividing the figure by 100. So, 10% becomes 10/100 = 0.1. The next step is to multiply the decimal figure by the full amount. So, 0.1 x 200 = 20. This gives you your answer. 10% of 200 is 20. In equation form, where Z is your answer, your equation is Z = (X/100) * Y.

value.name: What is 40 billion divided by 330 million?
value.snippet: To make it easier, remove the last six zeros of each number. Then, 40,000,000,000 divided by 330,000,000 becomes this: 40,000 divided by 330. Now, when we enter 40,000 ÷ 330 into our calculator, we get the answer to 40 billion divided by 330 million as follows: ≈ 121.2121. Billion divided by Million Calculator.
